blic affection as Queen Mother for nearly half a century. Even more influentially, it is the name of her daughter  Queen Elizabeth II  (  b. 1926 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Elisabeth","meanings":["The spelling of   Elizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Erzsebet de Galicia was born about 1160, in Galicia, Austria. She married Köten de Polowzes in 1180. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in 1239, in Ukraine, at the age of 80."},"et":{"ABT 1160–1239":"umbes 1160–1239","1160–1244":"1160–1244","1180–Female":"1180–Surnud","1160–1239":"1160–1239","1239":"1239","1244":"1244","1160":"1160","ABT 1160":"umbes 1160","1180":"1180","Galicia, Poland":"Galizien, Austria","Ukraine":"Ukraina","Polowzes, Poland":"Poola"},"fi":{"ABT 1160–1239":"noin 1160–1239","1160–1244":"1160–1244","1180–Female":"1180–Kuollut","1160–1239":"1160–1239","1239":"1239","1244":"1244","1160":"1160","ABT 1160":"noin 1160","1180":"1180","Galicia, Poland":"Galizien, Itävalta","Ukraine":"Ukraina","Polowzes, Poland":"Puola"},"fr":{"ABT 1160–1239":"environ 1160–1239","1160–1244":"1160–1244","1180–Female":"1180–Décédée","1160–1239":"1160–1239","1239":"1239","1244":"1244","1160":"1160","ABT 1160":"environ 1160","1180":"1180","Galicia, Poland":"Galicie, Autriche","Ukraine":"Ukraine","Polowzes, Poland":"Pologne","lifeSummary":"Erzsebet de Galicia est née environ 1160, à Galicie, Autriche. Elle a épousé Köten de Polowzes en 1180. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille. Elle est décédée en 1239, à Ukraine, à l’âge de 80 ans."},"de":{"ABT 1160–1239":"um 1160–1239","1160–1244":"1160–1244","1180–Fema